This isn't your average tapas bar and definitely my favorite in Barcelona.  First tip is to book reservations if you can.  What attracted us were the unique dishes.  Service was great and loved the decor.  Now let's talk about the food.Seabass Ceviche - Best dish we ordered.  I think I could've had about 3 of these to myself!Duck Timbale - DeliciousJamon - Cut real thin - reminded me of prociuttoThai beef noodle salad - Didn't have a lot of asian flavors but it was nice to mix it upSeafood Paella - Definitely one of the best we've had in Barcelona.  Muy bien!
